WEBVTT

00:51.120 --> 00:52.110
POPPY: <i>Once upon</i> a <i>time...</i>

00:52.320 --> 00:55.119
<i>in a happy forest,
in the happiest tree...</i>

00:55.880 --> 00:58.759
<i>lived the happiest creatures
the world has ever known.</i>

00:58.920 --> 00:59.876
<i>The Trolls.</i>

00:59.960 --> 01:01.712
(BOTH SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

01:01.800 --> 01:03.393
<i>They loved nothing more</i>

01:03.480 --> 01:05.949
<i>than to sing,
and dance, and hug.</i>

01:06.120 --> 01:08.634
<i>Dance, and hug,
and sing, and dance,</i>

01:08.760 --> 01:09.909
<i>and sing, and hug,
and dance...</i>

01:10.000 --> 01:10.990
<i>and hug, and dance,
and sing, and hug,</i>

01:11.120 --> 01:12.076
<i>and dance, and hug...</i>

01:12.160 --> 01:13.309
(CRYING)

01:14.320 --> 01:15.833
<i>But then one day,</i>

01:15.920 --> 01:17.479
<i>the Trolls
were discovered by...</i>

01:17.680 --> 01:19.114
a <i>Bergen!</i>

01:19.400 --> 01:20.390
(GRUNTS)

01:20.480 --> 01:22.232
<i>The Bergens
didn't know how to sing...</i>

01:22.320 --> 01:23.993
(SINGING OFF-KEY)
or dance---...

01:24.120 --> 01:25.679
<i>or even hug.</i>

01:26.120 --> 01:28.760
<i>They were the most miserable
creatures in all the land.</i>

01:28.840 --> 01:29.830
(CLOUD SIGHS)

01:29.960 --> 01:32.156
<i>And once they saw
how happy the Trolls were...</i>

01:32.360 --> 01:34.920
<i>they wanted some of that
happiness for themselves.</i>

01:35.000 --> 01:35.990
(SINGING)

01:36.120 --> 01:37.190
(SCREAMS)

01:38.000 --> 01:39.957
(ALL GASP)
Oh, my God!

01:40.280 --> 01:43.033
<i>Eating a Troll
made them feel so happy...</i>

01:43.200 --> 01:45.111
<i>they started a tradition.</i>

01:45.280 --> 01:47.351
<i>Once a year, every year...</i>

01:47.520 --> 01:49.875
<i>the Bergens would gather
around the Troll Tree...</i>

01:50.040 --> 01:51.872
<i>to taste happiness...</i>

01:52.040 --> 01:55.032
<i>on a holiday they called...</i>

01:55.200 --> 01:56.349
<i>Trollstice.</i>

01:59.320 --> 02:01.357
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)
(PANTING)

02:04.360 --> 02:06.033
(GRUNTING)

02:07.040 --> 02:08.473
(SNORING)

02:11.800 --> 02:12.790
Whoo!

02:12.880 --> 02:13.950
(BOTH GRUNT)

02:14.040 --> 02:15.678
Good morning, Daddy!

02:16.400 --> 02:17.390
Daddy, wake up!

02:17.560 --> 02:20.313
Daddy, wake up!
Wake up! Wake up, Daddy!

02:21.160 --> 02:23.356
Wake up, Daddy.

02:23.520 --> 02:25.670
Daddy! Daddy!
Daddy! Daddy!

02:25.840 --> 02:26.875
Daddy, wake up!

02:27.080 --> 02:28.150
(SCREAMS)

02:28.400 --> 02:30.391
Gristle! What time is it?

02:30.720 --> 02:33.997
It's Trollstice!

02:34.320 --> 02:38.075
Trollstice!
Our one day to be happy.

02:38.240 --> 02:39.230
Yeah!

02:39.320 --> 02:41.709
ALL: (CHANTING)
Trolls! Trolls! Trolls!

02:43.240 --> 02:45.151
Trolls! Trolls! Trolls!

02:50.680 --> 02:53.194
CHEF: Please give it up for
your Keeper of the Trolls...

02:53.400 --> 02:55.516
your Minister of Happiness...

02:55.680 --> 02:57.079
your Royal Chef...

02:58.280 --> 02:59.270
Me.

03:00.440 --> 03:01.430
ALL: Ooh!

03:04.040 --> 03:05.075
(ALL GASPING)

03:05.200 --> 03:06.520
(ALL CHEERING)

03:07.560 --> 03:10.439
This is
a very special Trollstice...

03:10.600 --> 03:14.195
as there is one amongst us
who has never tasted a Troll.

03:14.360 --> 03:16.670
Ooh, me!
She is talking about me!

03:16.880 --> 03:18.678
Prince Gristle...
(GASPS)

03:18.800 --> 03:20.598
...the time has come.

03:20.800 --> 03:21.790
It's okay, son.

03:21.960 --> 03:25.271
I remember being nervous
my first time.

03:25.440 --> 03:26.555
Okay-

03:26.720 --> 03:28.711
That's my boy.

03:32.120 --> 03:33.235
CHEF: It is my sacred duty...

03:33.440 --> 03:37.399
to initiate you in the
ways of true happiness.

03:40.600 --> 03:44.559
I have chosen an extra-special
Troll, just for you.

03:44.640 --> 03:45.630
(GASPS)

03:46.320 --> 03:48.436
The happiest,
the most positive...

03:49.160 --> 03:50.798
sweetest Troll of all.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.799
And because every prince
deserves a princess...

03:54.000 --> 03:57.914
I give you the one
they call Princess Poppy.

03:58.640 --> 04:00.631
Please make me happy,
Princess Poppy.

04:01.840 --> 04:02.910
What are you feeling?

04:04.680 --> 04:06.956
(SPITS) That one's rotten!

04:08.800 --> 04:10.074
Ifsfake?

04:10.320 --> 04:12.152
Fake?
Fake?

04:12.280 --> 04:13.270
(GRUNTS)

04:14.160 --> 04:15.309
They're gone?

04:15.680 --> 04:17.432
Where are they?

04:17.600 --> 04:19.829
Don't worry, sire.
We'll find them.

04:21.519 --> 04:23.193
I think I hear something!

04:24.840 --> 04:26.194
KING PEPPYI Go! Go!

04:26.920 --> 04:27.910
MALE TROLL 1: We got Poppy!

04:28.120 --> 04:29.349
MALE TROLL 2: Pass her to me!
Here comes Poppy!

04:29.520 --> 04:30.669
Here she is!

04:31.120 --> 04:32.838
Ah! There's my princess.

04:33.040 --> 04:34.110
Da-da. (LAUGHS)

04:34.520 --> 04:36.955
King Peppy, some of the others
can't keep up.

04:37.120 --> 04:39.475
No Troll left behind!

04:42.200 --> 04:43.349
Thank you, King Peppy!

04:44.120 --> 04:45.872
COOKIE: Thank you, King Peppy!
MALE TROLL 32 Thank you!

04:46.040 --> 04:47.110
(GRUNTS)

04:47.240 --> 04:48.355
Thank you, King Peppy.

04:48.520 --> 04:51.717
No Troll left behind!

04:51.880 --> 04:53.837
(BOTH SCREAM)

04:54.720 --> 04:56.199
Daddy, where are they?

04:56.400 --> 04:59.472
Don't just stand there!
Make my son happy!

04:59.640 --> 05:01.631
He will be happy!

05:01.720 --> 05:03.119
(ALL YELPING)

05:04.880 --> 05:05.870
(GRUNTS)

05:10.400 --> 05:13.631
(YELLS)

05:17.160 --> 05:19.231
(ALL SCREAMING)

05:23.240 --> 05:24.469
MALE TROLL: Where is he?

05:29.160 --> 05:31.595
I don't think
King Peppy made it.

05:31.760 --> 05:33.239
(ALL GASPING)

05:34.720 --> 05:38.998
KING PEPPY: When I say
no Troll left behind...

05:40.200 --> 05:45.070
I mean,
no Troll left behind!

05:45.160 --> 05:46.150
(ALL CHEERING)

05:47.840 --> 05:50.559
King Peppy,
where's Princess Poppy?

05:50.720 --> 05:52.836
Don't worry. She's safe.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.435
No Troll left behind!

05:55.520 --> 05:56.840
ALL: Aww!

05:56.960 --> 05:57.950
But we'll be a lot safer

05:58.080 --> 05:59.195
the further we get
from Bergen Town.

05:59.280 --> 06:01.191
Go, go! Hurry!

06:02.720 --> 06:05.394
<i>KING GRISTLE SR.:
That's right! Take her away!</i>

06:05.560 --> 06:07.198
Get her out of my sight!

06:07.360 --> 06:12.116
She is hereby banished
from Bergen Town forever.

06:12.800 --> 06:14.871
We can all be happy again.

06:15.040 --> 06:16.917
I'll find the Trolls!

06:18.720 --> 06:22.759
And shove them down
your ungrateful throats.

06:30.440 --> 06:32.317
But, Daddy...

06:32.880 --> 06:35.315
I never got to eat a Troll.

06:36.120 --> 06:38.873
What's gonna
make me happy now?

06:42.120 --> 06:43.110
Come here, son.

06:45.840 --> 06:46.989
Nothing.

06:47.160 --> 06:50.152
Absolutely nothing.

06:50.320 --> 06:54.678
You will never, ever, ever,
ever be happy.

06:55.440 --> 06:56.510
Never?

06:57.320 --> 06:58.310
Even

07:06.760 --> 07:07.750
(BRIDGET SIGHS)

07:10.680 --> 07:13.513
Here! Right here!

07:13.680 --> 07:17.514
This is where we will
rebuild our civilization.

07:17.600 --> 07:18.749
(ALL CHEERING)

07:18.840 --> 07:21.514
It has everything we need.

07:21.680 --> 07:24.149
Fresh air,
clean water...

07:24.320 --> 07:26.675
and sweet acoustics.

07:26.840 --> 07:28.114
(ECHOING)

07:28.200 --> 07:29.952
(BANGING RHYTHMICALLY)
(ALL CHEERING)

07:33.040 --> 07:36.476
(SINGING) Ba de ya
Say do you remember

07:36.680 --> 07:40.355
<i>Ba de ya
Dancing in September</i>

07:40.560 --> 07:44.872
<i>Ba de ya
Never was a cloudy day</i>

07:47.880 --> 07:51.475
POPPY: Twenty years ago today,
King Peppy made us safe...

07:51.640 --> 07:52.789
and now every Troll is free

07:52.880 --> 07:54.678
to be happy
and live in perfect...

07:55.000 --> 07:56.559
(SINGING) Harmony
Harmony

07:56.720 --> 07:58.074
<i>Harmony</i>

07:58.240 --> 08:00.356
And that's why
we hug every hour.

08:00.440 --> 08:01.430
Yep-

08:01.520 --> 08:03.318
I wish it was
every half hour.

08:03.480 --> 08:04.470
So do I.

08:04.640 --> 08:05.630
But that wouldn't leave
much time

08:05.720 --> 08:07.199
for singing and dancing,
now would it?

08:07.360 --> 08:10.512
Princess Poppy, do the Bergens
still want to eat us?

08:10.680 --> 08:12.478
You bet!
(ALL GASP)

08:12.560 --> 08:15.234
Butjust because it's the only
way they'll ever be happy.

08:15.400 --> 08:18.313
(SLURPS) Oh, no.
I do taste delicious.

08:18.480 --> 08:21.598
Isn't there anything else
to make them happy?

08:21.760 --> 08:23.512
Ooh. What about
having birthday parties?

08:23.680 --> 08:25.000
Or slumber parties?

08:25.160 --> 08:28.232
Or staring at your parents
while they sleep.

08:28.400 --> 08:29.390
(ALL GROANING)

08:29.480 --> 08:31.073
But I don't want
to be food.

08:31.280 --> 08:33.999
Don't worry.
No Troll ever will be.

08:34.200 --> 08:35.679
And that's why
we're celebrating

08:35.760 --> 08:37.751
with the biggest party ever.

08:37.919 --> 08:39.876
Everybody's gonna be there.

08:40.080 --> 08:41.832
Everybody?

08:42.400 --> 08:43.515
Everybody.

08:43.840 --> 08:45.592
(BANGING RHYTHMICALLY)

08:46.080 --> 08:47.718
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

08:48.440 --> 08:52.957
<i>(SINGING) Everybody, move
your hair and feel united</i>

08:53.240 --> 08:54.799
<i>Ohh!</i>

08:56.440 --> 09:00.911
<i>Everybody, shake your
hair and feel united</i>

09:01.400 --> 09:02.913
<i>Ohh!</i>

09:05.600 --> 09:06.556
<i>Yeah</i>

09:06.640 --> 09:07.755
<i>Everybody's coming
to the celebration</i>

09:07.920 --> 09:10.036
<i>I'ma hook you up
with the invitation</i>

09:10.120 --> 09:11.872
<i>Let your hair swing
and party with me</i>

09:12.040 --> 09:13.633
<i>No bad vibes
Just love, you'll see</i>

09:14.120 --> 09:17.875
<i>Do the D-A-N-C-E
One-two-three-four fight</i>

09:18.040 --> 09:20.793
<i>Stick to the B-E-A-T
Get ready to</i>

09:20.960 --> 09:21.950
<i>Ignite</i>

09:22.160 --> 09:26.074
<i>You are such a P-Y-T
Catching all the lights</i>

09:26.240 --> 09:29.790
<i>Just easy as A-B-C
That's how you make it right</i>

09:30.000 --> 09:31.832
<i>It ain't hard out here
When you're doing it right</i>

09:32.000 --> 09:34.310
<i>Put a smile on blast
That's the Troll life</i>

09:34.480 --> 09:36.153
<i>And I'm here
to help you through it</i>

09:36.280 --> 09:38.476
<i>Come on, Smidge,
I know you can do it</i>

09:38.680 --> 09:41.149
Your confidence
gives me strength.

09:44.120 --> 09:45.315
(TROLLS CHEERING)

09:48.640 --> 09:50.358
BIGGIE: Okay, Mr. Dinkies.

09:50.520 --> 09:52.158
Say, leaves!

09:52.360 --> 09:53.350
(SQUEAKS)

09:53.520 --> 09:54.510
(CAMERA CLICKS)

09:55.120 --> 09:56.474
Mmm.
Something's missing.

09:59.960 --> 10:00.950
ALL: That's it!

10:02.840 --> 10:04.433
<i>(SINGING) Don't stop, don't
stop Don't stop the beat</i>

10:04.600 --> 10:06.352
<i>I can't stop, can't stop
Can't stop the beat</i>

10:06.520 --> 10:08.272
<i>I won't stop, won't stop
Won't stop the beat</i>

10:08.440 --> 10:09.475
Go!

10:11.480 --> 10:15.872
<i>Everybody, shake your
hair and feel united</i>

10:16.200 --> 10:17.873
<i>Ohh!</i>

10:17.960 --> 10:21.715
<i>Sunshine day,
everybody's singing</i>

10:21.880 --> 10:23.200
<i>Sunshine day</i>

10:23.360 --> 10:28.196
<i>Everybody, move your
hair and feel united</i>

10:28.560 --> 10:32.554
<i>Ohh! Yeah, Ohh!</i>

10:37.120 --> 10:38.235
ALL: Yeah!

10:39.000 --> 10:40.957
(ALL PANTING)

10:41.480 --> 10:42.470
(EXHALES)

10:42.800 --> 10:44.393
(SLOW CLAPPING)

10:46.680 --> 10:47.875
Unbelievable, guys.

10:48.080 --> 10:49.991
Really, really great.
Good job.

10:50.160 --> 10:52.071
I could hear you
from a mile away!

10:52.240 --> 10:54.356
Good. I was worried we weren't
projecting enough.

10:54.520 --> 10:58.400
Poppy, if I can hear you,
so can the Bergens.

10:58.560 --> 10:59.550
Oh, boy.

10:59.720 --> 11:01.040
Here we go again.
Oh, Branch...

11:01.200 --> 11:02.395
You always ruin everything.

11:02.560 --> 11:04.039
Warning us
about the Bergens.

11:04.600 --> 11:05.590
No, I don't.

11:06.680 --> 11:08.751
The Bergens are coming!
(SCREAMING)

11:09.920 --> 11:11.911
The Bergens are coming!
(SCREAMING)

11:13.080 --> 11:14.912
The Bergens are coming!
(SCREAMING)

11:15.760 --> 11:18.070
Come on! We haven't seen
a Bergen in 20 years.

11:18.280 --> 11:19.429
They're not gonna find us.

11:19.600 --> 11:21.352
No, they're not
going to find me,

11:21.440 --> 11:23.078
becauselWlbe
in my highly camouflaged...

11:23.280 --> 11:25.920
heavily fortified,
Bergen-proof survival bunker.

11:26.120 --> 11:27.758
You mean you're not coming
to the party tonight?

11:27.920 --> 11:29.513
BOTH: But it's going to be
the biggest...

11:29.600 --> 11:30.590
The loudest...

11:30.680 --> 11:32.512
The craziest party ever!

11:32.600 --> 11:33.749
(ALL CHEERING)

11:33.920 --> 11:35.752
Big? Loud?

11:35.960 --> 11:36.950
Crazy?

11:37.120 --> 11:39.236
You're just gonna lead
the Bergens right to us!

11:39.400 --> 11:41.118
Are you sure
you wanna invite

11:41.240 --> 11:43.072
this party pooper
t0 poop on your party?

11:43.240 --> 11:45.959
Yes. I think everyone deserves
to be happy.

11:46.120 --> 11:47.394
I don't do happy.

11:47.600 --> 11:50.240
Branch, I know you have
happiness inside you.

11:50.400 --> 11:52.471
You just need
our help to find it.

11:54.640 --> 11:58.110
<i>(SINGING) Celebrate
freedom from the Bergens</i>

12:08.080 --> 12:09.912
What do you say, Branch?

12:12.960 --> 12:14.633
(ALL GASP)
Oh, my God.

12:14.800 --> 12:17.155
I wouldn't be caught dead at
your party, but you will be.

12:17.320 --> 12:18.833
Caught and dead.

12:19.000 --> 12:20.070
CREEK: Whoa, whoa.

12:20.240 --> 12:22.151
Easy, Branch. Easy.

12:24.680 --> 12:27.115
Thank you for providing
safe passage, brother.

12:27.280 --> 12:28.679
Namaste.

12:28.840 --> 12:31.593
Okay, first of all, mate,
thanks for sharing

12:31.680 --> 12:33.512
your unique perspective
on things.

12:33.680 --> 12:34.670
Again.

12:34.840 --> 12:35.989
(SNICKERING)

12:36.120 --> 12:37.349
But, just for now,
why don't you try on

12:37.440 --> 12:38.794
some positivity, eh?

12:38.960 --> 12:41.634
A little positivity
might go with that vest.

12:41.840 --> 12:42.989
Okay, fine.

12:43.160 --> 12:46.198
I'm positive you all
are going to get eaten.

12:46.520 --> 12:47.590
(CHIMING)

12:47.680 --> 12:49.591
Hug time!
It is hug time.

12:49.760 --> 12:51.671
ALL: Hug time!

12:51.840 --> 12:53.751
Oh, that feels good.
Our hearts are synchronizing!

12:53.960 --> 12:56.190
(S I N G I N G)
<i>I</i> can squeeze you forever

12:56.360 --> 12:58.590
(BRANCH GRUNTING)

12:58.680 --> 13:00.796
Someday,
when the Bergens find us...

13:00.960 --> 13:03.474
and the survival of every
Troll is in your hands...

13:03.640 --> 13:04.789
I sure hope the answer

13:04.880 --> 13:06.109
is singing, dancing,
and hugging...

13:06.280 --> 13:07.873
because that's all you know
how to do.

13:08.040 --> 13:11.192
That is not true!
Poppy can also scrapbook.

13:11.360 --> 13:14.113
I can't believe you're
gonna be queen one day.

13:16.720 --> 13:19.280
Tune out his
negative vibrations, Poppy.

13:19.400 --> 13:20.549
They're toxic.

13:20.720 --> 13:23.838
Some folks just
don't want to be happy.

13:24.000 --> 13:25.115
I guess.

13:25.320 --> 13:26.435
You guessed right.

13:26.760 --> 13:27.875
Boop.

13:28.720 --> 13:30.154
(ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING)

13:30.480 --> 13:31.709
(TROLLS CHEERING)

13:31.800 --> 13:33.154
Yeah!

13:36.160 --> 13:37.798
(GRUNTING)

13:38.560 --> 13:40.392
Whoo! I love you so much!

13:46.840 --> 13:47.557
Yeah!

13:48.320 --> 13:49.879
Whoo! Glitter!

13:51.880 --> 13:53.598
(ALL GASP)
(MUSIC STOPS)

13:55.200 --> 13:56.873
YOLO!
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

13:57.240 --> 13:58.560
(ALL CHEERING)

14:08.080 --> 14:09.070
(SCOFFS)

14:13.000 --> 14:14.274
More glitter!

14:16.680 --> 14:19.354
Turn it up!

14:28.800 --> 14:30.120
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

14:38.120 --> 14:40.589
POPPY: I can't hear you!
(TROLLS CHEERING)

14:44.800 --> 14:46.473
Trolls.

14:46.960 --> 14:48.314
POPPY: Okay, everyone.

14:48.480 --> 14:50.471
I just want to
take a moment...

14:50.640 --> 14:52.233
and get a little real.

14:52.400 --> 14:53.390
BIGGIE: Poppy!

14:53.480 --> 14:55.153
She's my friend!
I know her!

14:55.240 --> 14:56.594
(ALL SHUSHING)
(SQUEAKS)

14:56.720 --> 14:57.710
(KING PEPPY CLEARS THROAT)

14:57.800 --> 15:02.476
I'd like to take a second
to celebrate our king...

15:02.560 --> 15:03.550
my father...

15:04.560 --> 15:06.836
who, 20 years ago
this night...

15:07.000 --> 15:09.753
saved all of us
from those dreaded...

15:09.840 --> 15:10.830
(LOUD FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

15:10.960 --> 15:11.995
(ALL GASPING)

15:14.640 --> 15:15.630
(CRASHING)

15:16.280 --> 15:17.509
Bergens.

15:20.160 --> 15:21.195
(ALL GASP)

15:22.720 --> 15:23.835
Gotcha.

15:28.160 --> 15:29.594
Uh...

15:29.680 --> 15:30.795
Cupcake?

15:34.560 --> 15:36.551
Run!
(ALL CLAMORING)

15:36.640 --> 15:37.630
Run! Run!

15:38.440 --> 15:39.430
PQppy, help!

15:40.040 --> 15:41.030
Mr. Dinkies?

15:41.200 --> 15:43.111
Has anybody seen Mr.
Dinkies? (SQUEAKS)

15:43.200 --> 15:45.032
(YELPING)
POPPY: Biggie!

15:45.200 --> 15:48.192
Blend in! Blend in!
Blend in!

15:48.520 --> 15:49.476
SCARED TROLL: Poppy!

15:49.560 --> 15:51.551
(GASPS)
MALE TROLL: Run!

15:54.560 --> 15:55.675
POPPY: Run, Smidge!

15:55.760 --> 15:56.750
Oh, my God!

15:56.840 --> 15:58.239
(BOTH GRUNTING)

15:58.360 --> 15:59.873
(BOTH SCREAMING)

15:59.960 --> 16:00.950
TROLL CHILD: Poppy, help!

16:01.040 --> 16:02.269
Hurry!
(SCREAMS)

16:02.360 --> 16:04.033
Go!Go!Go!

16:04.600 --> 16:05.749
Phew... Whoa!

16:05.880 --> 16:06.836
Cooper!

16:06.920 --> 16:08.718
CREEK: Everyone,
minimize your auras!

16:08.880 --> 16:10.393
(GASPS) Creek!
No! Poppy!

16:11.160 --> 16:12.230
(GRUNTING)

16:12.440 --> 16:13.714
Hold on.
POPPY!

16:14.880 --> 16:16.393
CREEK: No!
Creek!

16:16.560 --> 16:17.994
(SCREAMING)
MALE TROLL: Ow!

16:19.840 --> 16:21.274
Hmm.

16:21.400 --> 16:23.198
Bad Bergen!
Bad, bad Bergen.

16:23.280 --> 16:24.315
Ah...

16:24.400 --> 16:26.038
(GASPS)
Bad, bad Bergen!

16:26.120 --> 16:27.110
Dad!

16:27.440 --> 16:29.317
(CHEF GRUNTING)

16:29.400 --> 16:31.232
Whoa... (SIGHS)
(SHUSHING)

16:32.520 --> 16:33.749
(GROANS)

16:40.760 --> 16:41.750
(SCOFFS)

16:45.800 --> 16:48.474
Thanks for throwing
the biggest...

16:48.640 --> 16:50.597
the loudest...

16:50.760 --> 16:52.831
The craziest party ever.

16:52.920 --> 16:53.910
(GROANING)

16:58.480 --> 16:59.754
(GRUNTS)

17:35.960 --> 17:37.837
Is it coming back?

17:38.080 --> 17:40.151
What are we gonna do now?

17:40.640 --> 17:43.200
We have to find a new home.
Everyone, hurry.

17:43.360 --> 17:45.510
We have to leave
before the Bergens come back.

17:45.680 --> 17:46.795
We have to rescue them.

17:47.000 --> 17:48.479
No, Poppy.
we have to run.

17:48.600 --> 17:50.159
Now, let's go, everyone.
Come on!

17:50.320 --> 17:53.517
What about
"No Troll left behind"?

17:54.840 --> 17:55.875
I'm sorry, POPPY-

17:56.040 --> 17:57.314
That was a long time ago.

17:57.440 --> 17:59.954
And I'm not the king
I once was.

18:02.000 --> 18:03.149
Then I'll go.

18:03.320 --> 18:04.833
I'll go and save them.

18:05.000 --> 18:07.514
No, Poppy.
It's too dangerous.

18:07.680 --> 18:09.114
I have to at least try.

18:09.280 --> 18:12.159
No. You can't go to
Bergen Town by yourself.

18:12.360 --> 18:13.794
It's impossible.

18:18.960 --> 18:22.510
MALE <i>TROLL ON RECORDING: (SINGING)
Celebrate freedom from the Bergens</i>

18:24.480 --> 18:28.189
<i>Celebrate freedom
from the Bergens</i>

18:34.520 --> 18:36.477
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
(GASPS)

18:38.000 --> 18:39.115
(RECORDED MESSAGES
PLAYING SIMULTANEOUSLY)

18:39.200 --> 18:41.032
<i>Branch, you're invited!</i>

18:41.200 --> 18:42.395
No! No! No! (SHUSHING)

18:45.360 --> 18:46.714
Branch! Branch! Branch!

18:46.880 --> 18:48.359
Branch, are you
in there? Huh?

18:48.560 --> 18:50.039
I'm not going to your party.

18:50.200 --> 18:51.235
The party's over.

18:51.400 --> 18:52.993
We just got
attacked by a Bergen.

18:53.160 --> 18:54.355
I knew it.

18:55.080 --> 18:56.070
(POPPY GASPS)

19:06.240 --> 19:07.230
Branch!
Shh.

19:07.720 --> 19:09.199
I have to tell you something.
Shh.

19:09.840 --> 19:10.796
I was just gonna...

19:10.920 --> 19:12.752
(TUTTING) Shh! Shh!

19:14.440 --> 19:15.430
What?

19:15.560 --> 19:17.073
What could be
so important that it's worth

19:17.200 --> 19:18.599
leading the Bergen
right to us?

19:18.840 --> 19:19.830
The Bergen's gone!

19:19.920 --> 19:21.797
You don't know that.
It could still be out there.

19:21.960 --> 19:22.950
Watching.

19:23.080 --> 19:24.070
Waiting.

19:24.240 --> 19:25.878
Listening.

19:26.280 --> 19:27.395
No. It left!

19:27.600 --> 19:30.069
It took Cooper, and Smidge,
and Fuzzbert...

19:30.240 --> 19:31.958
and Satin,
and Chenille, and Biggie,

19:32.080 --> 19:34.037
and Guy Diamond,
and Creek!

19:34.120 --> 19:35.190
Mmm.

19:35.280 --> 19:36.793
Which is why
I have to ask you.

19:37.760 --> 19:39.751
Will you go to Bergen Town
with me and save everyone?

19:39.920 --> 19:41.115
What? No.

19:41.320 --> 19:43.311
Branch, you can't say no.
They're your friends.

19:43.440 --> 19:45.113
Uh-uh-uh.
They're your friends.

19:45.280 --> 19:47.078
I'm staying right here
in my bunker where it's safe.

19:47.240 --> 19:48.275
Oh, that's great.

19:48.440 --> 19:50.431
You're the one guy who knows more
about Bergens than anyone...

19:50.560 --> 19:51.595
but when
we finally need you,

19:51.720 --> 19:53.119
you just want
to hide here forever?

19:53.280 --> 19:55.715
Forever? Pfft. No.

19:55.840 --> 19:57.069
Oh!

19:57.640 --> 19:58.630
Yeah...

19:58.720 --> 19:59.790
I really only have
enough supplies

19:59.920 --> 20:02.070
down here
to last me 10 years...

20:02.240 --> 20:04.800
11 if I'm willing to store
and drink my own sweat.

20:04.960 --> 20:06.439
Which I am.

20:06.640 --> 20:08.233
You all said
I was crazy, huh?

20:08.400 --> 20:10.277
Well, who's crazy now?

20:10.800 --> 20:12.996
Me. Crazy prepared.

20:13.800 --> 20:15.791
I'm sorry.
I should have listened to you.

20:15.960 --> 20:17.598
You told me
not to throw the party,

20:17.680 --> 20:19.114
and I threw it anyway.

20:19.320 --> 20:20.640
And it's my fault
they were taken.

20:20.800 --> 20:22.313
And now
I don't know what to do.

20:22.640 --> 20:24.950
Why don't you try
scrapbooking them to freedom?

20:25.920 --> 20:27.354
Solid burn, Branch.

20:29.160 --> 20:31.470
Well, thanks anyway.

20:31.640 --> 20:33.790
Hey, anytime, Poppy.
See you in 10 years.

20:48.680 --> 20:49.829
(PLATFORM LOWERING)

20:51.800 --> 20:52.995
Oh, hey, Branch?

20:53.160 --> 20:55.310
Just wondering
if I could borrow something.

20:55.440 --> 20:56.430
(SIGHS) What?

20:56.520 --> 20:57.874
Your bunker.
What?

20:58.040 --> 21:00.111
Okay, everybody.
Come on in!

21:00.200 --> 21:01.349
(ALL CLAMORING)

21:01.480 --> 21:02.515
Hi, Branch!

21:03.520 --> 21:05.033
No!No!No!

21:05.240 --> 21:07.197
Whoa, wait!
Poppy, what are you doing?

21:07.360 --> 21:08.589
You said
you have enough provisions

21:08.680 --> 21:10.193
to last 10 years, right?

21:10.360 --> 21:12.510
Yes, to last me
10 years. Me!

21:12.680 --> 21:13.829
It'll last them two weeks!

21:14.040 --> 21:15.553
Then I guess I better hurry.

21:15.720 --> 21:16.710
Wait, wait, wait!

21:16.840 --> 21:18.353
You won't last a day
out there.

21:18.520 --> 21:20.477
And you won't last a day
in here.

21:21.480 --> 21:22.993
ALL: (CHANTING)
Chug, chug, chug!

21:23.160 --> 21:24.480
(ALL LAUGHING)

21:26.520 --> 21:28.875
Solid burn, returned.
(GLASS SHATTERING)

21:29.040 --> 21:30.678
MALE TROLL: Sorry, Branch!

21:31.240 --> 21:32.560
(STAMMERING) Uh, Poppy, wait.

21:33.880 --> 21:35.393
Please be careful.

21:35.600 --> 21:38.672
Don't worry, Dad.
I can do this.

21:39.880 --> 21:41.871
I love you, POPPY-

21:42.720 --> 21:44.597
I love you too, Dad.

21:49.240 --> 21:51.595
They grow up so fast.

21:52.080 --> 21:53.832
Bye, everybody!
See you soon!

21:54.040 --> 21:56.236
ALL: Good luck,
Princess Poppy!

21:57.760 --> 22:01.071
(SOFTLY) And three, two, one.

22:03.560 --> 22:04.550
Hug time!

22:04.760 --> 22:05.909
No.

22:06.080 --> 22:07.400
ALL: (CHANTING) Hug time!
Hug time! Hug time!

22:07.560 --> 22:09.551
No! No!

22:13.040 --> 22:14.951
POPPY: <i>With her friends
safely hidden...</i>

22:15.120 --> 22:17.760
<i>Princess Poppy set off
to rescue her other friends...</i>

22:17.920 --> 22:21.072
<i>confident she'd make it
to Bergen Town on her own.</i>

22:21.360 --> 22:22.759
(BERGEN SNARLING)

22:24.200 --> 22:26.430
<i>Convinced she'd make it
to Bergen Town.</i>

22:29.080 --> 22:30.593
(SIGHS) Um...

22:33.280 --> 22:36.432
Totally sure she'd make it
to Bergen Town.

22:36.880 --> 22:38.154
Mmm...

22:39.600 --> 22:40.954
(SIGHS)

22:47.600 --> 22:50.114
<i>(SINGING) I really
hope I can do it</i>

22:50.280 --> 22:52.954
<i>'Cause they're
all depending on me</i>

22:53.640 --> 22:58.157
<i>I know that I must leave
the only home I've ever known</i>

22:58.320 --> 23:00.436
<i>And brave
the dangers of the forest</i>

23:00.520 --> 23:03.353
<i>Saving them
before they're eaten</i>

23:04.080 --> 23:09.473
<i>I mean,
how hard can that be?</i>

23:09.600 --> 23:11.159
(SCREAMS)

23:15.280 --> 23:16.634
(GRUNTS)

23:19.000 --> 23:20.832
<i>(SINGING)
Looking up at</i> a <i>sunny sky</i>

23:21.000 --> 23:23.196
<i>So shiny and blue
and there's a butterfly</i>

23:23.360 --> 23:26.159
<i>Well, isn't that
a super fantastic sign?</i>

23:32.680 --> 23:33.670
(BURPS)

23:34.280 --> 23:37.477
<i>(SINGING) It's gonna
be</i> a <i>fantastic day</i>

23:37.680 --> 23:39.637
<i>Such marvelousness
it's gonna bring</i>

23:39.800 --> 23:41.996
<i>Got a pocket full of songs
that I'm gonna sing</i>

23:42.160 --> 23:44.959
<i>And I'm ready
to take on anything</i>

23:45.120 --> 23:46.633
<i>Hooray!</i>

23:46.800 --> 23:51.317
<i>Some super fun surprise
around each corner</i>

23:51.400 --> 23:54.358
<i>Just riding on a rainbow</i>

23:54.520 --> 23:56.796
<i>I'm gonna be okay</i>

23:56.960 --> 23:59.395
<i>Hey! I'm not
giving up today</i>

24:00.360 --> 24:02.112
<i>There's nothing
getting in my way</i>

24:02.560 --> 24:04.198
<i>And if you knock,
knock me over</i>

24:04.360 --> 24:05.509
<i>I will get back up again</i>

24:05.640 --> 24:06.869
(SQUAWKING)

24:07.040 --> 24:09.919
<i>Oh! If something goes
a little wrong</i>

24:10.080 --> 24:12.117
<i>Well you can go ahead
and bring it on</i>

24:12.280 --> 24:13.759
<i>'Cause if you knock,
knock me over</i>

24:13.920 --> 24:16.673
<i>I will get back up again</i>

24:16.760 --> 24:18.159
(BOTH CHIRPING)

24:18.280 --> 24:19.679
<i>Whoa, oh, oh, oh</i>

24:19.760 --> 24:20.875
<i>Oh, get back up again</i>

24:22.200 --> 24:24.760
<i>Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh</i>

24:24.880 --> 24:26.029
Ahh!

24:26.160 --> 24:28.151
<i>I'm marching along
I've got confidence</i>

24:28.360 --> 24:30.431
<i>I'm cooler than
a pack of peppermints</i>

24:30.600 --> 24:33.035
<i>And I haven't been
this excited</i>

24:33.240 --> 24:35.550
<i>Since I can't remember when</i>

24:35.720 --> 24:40.191
<i>I'm off
on this remarkable adventure</i>

24:40.360 --> 24:42.829
<i>Just riding on a rainbow</i>

24:43.040 --> 24:45.236
<i>But what if
it's all a big mistake?</i>

24:45.400 --> 24:47.914
<i>What if
it's more than I can take?</i>

24:48.080 --> 24:49.673
<i>No, I can't think that way</i>

24:49.880 --> 24:53.919
<i>'Cause I know that I'm really,
really, really gonna be okay</i>

24:54.080 --> 24:57.198
<i>Hey! I'm not
giving up today</i>

24:57.360 --> 24:59.749
<i>There's nothing getting
in my way</i>

24:59.920 --> 25:00.910
<i>And if you knock,
knock me over</i>

25:01.080 --> 25:04.072
<i>I will get back up again</i>

25:05.120 --> 25:06.872
<i>Oh, if something goes
a little wrong</i>

25:06.960 --> 25:09.076
<i>Well you can go ahead
and bring it on</i>

25:09.240 --> 25:10.913
<i>'Cause if you knock,
knock me over</i>

25:11.080 --> 25:13.993
<i>I will get back up again</i>

25:14.280 --> 25:16.749
<i>Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh</i>

25:16.880 --> 25:18.279
<i>Oh, get back up again</i>

25:19.160 --> 25:21.310
<i>Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh</i>

25:21.440 --> 25:22.430
<i>Oh</i>

25:22.600 --> 25:24.432
I'm okay!

25:24.560 --> 25:26.631
<i>(SINGING)
Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh</i>

25:26.760 --> 25:27.750
<i>Oh</i>

25:27.920 --> 25:28.990
<i>And if you knock,
knock me over</i>

25:29.120 --> 25:30.394
<i>You knock, knock me over</i>

25:30.560 --> 25:35.111
<i>I will get back up again</i>

25:37.080 --> 25:38.070
(GROANS)

26:04.720 --> 26:05.710
(ALL GASP)

26:09.320 --> 26:10.310
(GROWLING)

26:12.160 --> 26:13.195
(GRUNTS)

26:13.480 --> 26:14.515
(SCREECHING)

26:15.400 --> 26:16.390
(GRUNTS)

26:17.320 --> 26:18.310
Hmm?

26:18.920 --> 26:20.877
(SHUDDERS)
(SCREECHING)

26:22.640 --> 26:23.675
(GRUNTING)

26:27.520 --> 26:28.635
Get back!

26:37.040 --> 26:38.030
Whoa.

26:42.160 --> 26:43.992
(SIGHS) Huh?

26:44.560 --> 26:46.233
Oh no! Poppy?

26:47.560 --> 26:48.550
Hang on!

26:52.360 --> 26:53.350
(POWERING UP)

26:53.520 --> 26:54.840
(ZAPPING)

26:54.920 --> 26:56.831
<i>(SINGING)
Get back up again</i>

26:57.000 --> 26:58.195
Branch, my man!

26:58.360 --> 26:59.350
You are right on time.

26:59.520 --> 27:01.511
Oh, right.
Like you knew I was coming.

27:01.720 --> 27:03.154
Yes! I figured after
the third hug time...

27:03.320 --> 27:04.993
getting eaten by a Bergen
wouldn't seem so bad.

27:05.160 --> 27:07.879
And I figured there was no way
you could do this by yourself.

27:08.040 --> 27:09.075
Guess we were both right.

27:09.200 --> 27:11.396
Hmm. All right.
Let's do this!

27:11.560 --> 27:12.630
Sooner we get to Bergen Town,

27:12.720 --> 27:13.994
sooner we can rescue
everybody...

27:14.120 --> 27:15.190
and make it home safely.

27:15.400 --> 27:17.277
Wait, wait, wait.
What's your plan?

27:17.440 --> 27:18.589
I just told you.
To rescue everyone

27:18.720 --> 27:19.710
and make it home safely.

27:19.880 --> 27:22.269
Okay. That's not a plan.
That's a wish list.

27:22.440 --> 27:24.511
Oh! I suppose
you have a plan.

27:24.720 --> 27:25.710
<i>(CLEARS T HRO AT)</i>

27:25.840 --> 27:27.114
First...

27:27.680 --> 27:28.829
<i>we get to
the edge of Bergen Town</i>

27:28.920 --> 27:30.433
<i>without being spotted.</i>

27:30.600 --> 27:31.954
<i>Then, we get inside
by sneaking</i>

27:32.080 --> 27:33.195
<i>through the old
escape tunnels...</i>

27:33.360 --> 27:35.271
<i>which will then lead us
to the Troll Tree...</i>

27:35.440 --> 27:36.475
<i>right before we get caught,</i>

27:36.560 --> 27:38.039
<i>and suffer
a miserable death...</i>

27:38.200 --> 27:40.794
<i>at the hands of a horrible,
bloodthirsty Bergen!</i>

27:40.960 --> 27:43.236
Hold on a second,
are you scrapbooking my plan?

27:43.400 --> 27:45.755
Uh-huh. Yeah. Almost...

27:45.920 --> 27:46.910
done!

27:47.720 --> 27:48.915
RECORDED VOICES: We <i>did</i> it!

27:56.920 --> 27:58.274
There will be no more...

28:00.240 --> 28:01.469
scrapbooking.

28:02.120 --> 28:03.713
(POPPY SINGING)

28:04.480 --> 28:05.914
BRANCH: Do you have to sing?

28:06.120 --> 28:07.633
POPPY: I always sing
when I'm in a good mood.

28:07.800 --> 28:09.279
BRANCH: Do you
have to be in a good mood?

28:09.440 --> 28:10.430
POPPY: Why wouldn't I be?

28:10.600 --> 28:13.114
By this time tomorrow,
I'll be with all my friends!

28:13.280 --> 28:15.430
Oh, I wonder
what they're doing right now.

28:15.600 --> 28:16.999
Probably being digested.

28:17.160 --> 28:18.958
They're alive, Branch.
I know it!

28:19.120 --> 28:20.474
You don't know
anything, Poppy.

28:20.640 --> 28:22.278
And I can't wait to see
the look on your face...

28:22.440 --> 28:23.510
when you realize the world

28:23.600 --> 28:25.238
isn't all cupcakes
and rainbows.

28:25.320 --> 28:26.310
'Cause it isn't.

28:26.800 --> 28:28.313
Bad things happen...

28:28.480 --> 28:30.949
and there's nothing
you can do about it.

28:31.920 --> 28:34.673
Hey, I know it's not
all cupcakes and rainbows.

28:34.840 --> 28:37.116
But I'd rather go through life
thinking that it mostly is...

28:37.280 --> 28:38.600
instead of being like you.

28:38.760 --> 28:40.273
You don't sing,
you don't dance.

28:40.440 --> 28:43.319
So grey all the time!
What happened to you?

28:43.440 --> 28:44.430
Shh.

28:45.200 --> 28:46.315
A Bergen?

28:46.840 --> 28:47.955
(SOFTLY) Maybe.

28:52.000 --> 28:53.479
There's no Bergen,
is there?

28:53.880 --> 28:55.951
You just said that
so I'd stop talking.

28:56.600 --> 28:57.590
(SOFTLY) Maybe.

29:11.960 --> 29:13.280
(SIGHS)

29:20.800 --> 29:22.677
So special.

29:24.360 --> 29:25.555
Good night, Cooper.

29:26.000 --> 29:28.674
Good night, Smidge.
Good night, Fuzzbert.

29:28.840 --> 29:30.877
Good night, Satin.
Good night, Chenille.

29:31.080 --> 29:33.549
Good night, Biggie.
Good night, DJ.

29:33.720 --> 29:35.074
Good night, Guy Diamond.

29:35.200 --> 29:37.032
(CHUCKLES) Good night, Creek.

29:37.520 --> 29:38.510
Boop.

29:38.680 --> 29:40.034
And good night, Poppy.

29:48.680 --> 29:51.718
BRANCH:
Don't even think about it.

29:53.520 --> 29:54.715
(MOUTHING)

30:02.400 --> 30:06.394
<i>(SINGING) Stars shining
bright above you</i>

30:06.560 --> 30:08.551
Really? Seriously?
More singing?

30:08.720 --> 30:11.553
Yes, seriously!
Singing helps me relax.

30:11.720 --> 30:13.040
Maybe you ought to try it.

30:13.200 --> 30:15.476
I don't sing,
and I don't relax.

30:15.560 --> 30:17.392
This is the way I am,
and I like it.

30:17.560 --> 30:19.756
I also like a little silence.

30:23.960 --> 30:25.519
(UKULELE PLAYING)

30:29.040 --> 30:32.396
<i>(SINGING)
Hello Darkness, my old friend</i>

30:33.240 --> 30:35.629
<i>I've come
to talk with you again</i>

30:36.560 --> 30:37.755
Hello.

30:37.920 --> 30:41.436
<i>Because a vision
softly creeping</i>

30:42.600 --> 30:47.231
<i>Left its seeds
while I was sleeping</i>

30:47.400 --> 30:52.918
<i>And the vision
that was planted in my brain</i>

30:54.080 --> 30:56.469
<i>Still remains</i>

30:57.240 --> 31:01.120
<i>Within the sound...</i>

31:02.560 --> 31:05.074
<i>ofsflence</i>

31:10.760 --> 31:11.955
May I?

31:23.960 --> 31:26.236
POPPY: So one of these tunnels
leads to the Troll Tree.

31:26.360 --> 31:27.350
BRANCH: That's right.

31:27.440 --> 31:28.953
There's so many of them.

31:29.320 --> 31:30.594
I wonder which one.

31:30.760 --> 31:32.194
I don't know.

31:32.360 --> 31:35.512
MALE VOICE:
Choose a hole wisely!

31:35.680 --> 31:38.798
For one will lead
to Bergen Town...

31:39.000 --> 31:41.992
and the others,
to certain death. (ECHOING)

31:42.160 --> 31:43.150
Who said that?

31:43.640 --> 31:45.836
MALE VOICE: It was...

31:46.640 --> 31:47.596
me.

31:47.680 --> 31:50.957
Hey, guys, how's it going?
Welcome to the root tunnels.

31:51.120 --> 31:52.190
Uh, I just wanted to warn you.

31:52.360 --> 31:54.476
One of these tunnels leads
to the Troll Tree...

31:54.680 --> 31:56.671
and the others to
(IN DEEP VOICE) certain death,

31:56.800 --> 31:57.995
death, death, death...

31:58.120 --> 31:59.918
(IMITATES ECHO FADING)

32:00.000 --> 32:02.150
Do you think you can tell us
which is the right one?

32:02.320 --> 32:03.390
You bet!

32:03.480 --> 32:04.436
Great!
No, that's okay.

32:04.520 --> 32:05.510
We're fine, thanks!

32:05.640 --> 32:06.630
Branch. (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

32:06.720 --> 32:07.835
He's trying to help us.

32:08.000 --> 32:09.513
I don't like the looks of him.

32:09.680 --> 32:11.830
I mean,
who wears socks with no shoes?

32:13.240 --> 32:15.390
He seems to know
what he's talking about.

32:16.360 --> 32:18.237
Okay, fine.

32:18.640 --> 32:19.994
Which way do we go?

32:20.160 --> 32:21.639
First, you have to
give me a high five.

32:21.720 --> 32:22.790
Then I'll tell you.

32:22.880 --> 32:23.950
What?

32:24.040 --> 32:25.030
Oh, I love high fives.
I'll do it.

32:25.200 --> 32:26.520
Oh, I know you'll do it.

32:27.320 --> 32:28.310
But will he?

32:28.680 --> 32:30.557
All right, dumpy diapers,
up high!

32:30.760 --> 32:32.034
Nope, I don't do high fives.

32:32.200 --> 32:33.679
Slap it, boss.
Not gonna happen.

32:33.840 --> 32:35.399
Party on the top floor.
Nope.

32:35.560 --> 32:36.880
Little slappy.
Make daddy happy-

32:37.040 --> 32:38.110
That's weird.

32:38.200 --> 32:39.713
Come on,
just one little high five.

32:39.880 --> 32:41.598
Oh, no, thanks. I'm good.

32:41.760 --> 32:42.875
Here, just do this...

32:43.360 --> 32:44.555
But with your hand.

32:44.720 --> 32:45.869
Thank you
for that demonstration.

32:46.040 --> 32:48.077
Really cleared up exactly
what I will not be doing.

32:48.240 --> 32:50.072
Branch, it's a high five.

32:50.280 --> 32:51.793
The others
lead to certain death.

32:51.880 --> 32:53.359
Get perspective.

32:56.360 --> 32:58.715
(SIGHS) One high five
and then you'll tell us

32:58.840 --> 33:00.114
which tunnel to take, right?

33:00.280 --> 33:01.395
So easy.

33:01.560 --> 33:02.880
(G RU NTS) Okay, fine!

33:03.040 --> 33:04.235
Ooh. Too slow.

33:04.400 --> 33:05.549
Too slow?

33:05.680 --> 33:07.114
(LAUGHS)

33:08.200 --> 33:09.235
(CHUCKLES) Classic.

33:09.600 --> 33:11.238
No, no. All right.

33:11.400 --> 33:13.550
I'm gonna let you slide
with a fist bump.

33:13.960 --> 33:16.031
Whoo. Shark attack!
Nom-nom-nom-nom. Jellyfish!

33:16.200 --> 33:17.713
Hand sandwich. Turkey.
Snowman. Dolphin.

33:17.800 --> 33:19.234
Helicopter. Last Supper.
Monkey in a zoo.

33:19.400 --> 33:20.595
What?
Gear shift

33:20.760 --> 33:22.239
(IMITATES GEARS SHIFTING)

33:26.280 --> 33:27.714
(BOTH LAUGHING)

33:30.040 --> 33:32.316
Okay, okay, okay.
Now I'm thinking we hug.

33:33.480 --> 33:34.595
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

33:35.760 --> 33:36.238
(SCREAMING)

33:36.280 --> 33:37.634
BRANCH: That's right.
You better run, Cloud!

33:37.760 --> 33:38.909
POPPY: Wait!

33:39.120 --> 33:40.394
I'm gonna
tear your little cloud arms...

33:40.560 --> 33:42.073
off your cloud body,

33:42.160 --> 33:43.275
and high five
your face with them!

33:43.880 --> 33:45.598
POPPY: He's just a cloud!

33:45.760 --> 33:47.592
BRANCH: Get back here!
POPPY: Branch! He can help us!

33:47.760 --> 33:48.795
BRANCH: Come back!

33:49.000 --> 33:50.035
POPPY: Run, Cloud Guy!

33:50.120 --> 33:51.110
I'm gonna kill you!

33:51.280 --> 33:52.918
Ta-da! We're here!

33:53.120 --> 33:54.110
Phew...

33:54.240 --> 33:56.277
You guys are a lot of fun.
You know, I gotta go.

33:56.440 --> 33:58.033
Got some cloud stuff
to take care of.

33:58.120 --> 33:59.872
Catch you on the way back?

33:59.960 --> 34:00.995
Unless...

34:01.440 --> 34:03.078
you die.
(IMITATES ECHO FADING)

34:04.960 --> 34:06.633
The Troll Tree.

34:06.800 --> 34:08.473
Bergen Town.

34:14.880 --> 34:16.632
<i>(CLINT EASTWOOD PLAYING)</i>

34:23.480 --> 34:25.710
<i>ALL: (SINGING) I ain't happy
I'm feeling glad</i>

34:25.880 --> 34:30.272
<i>I got sunshine in a bag
I'm useless</i>

34:30.440 --> 34:34.320
<i>But not for long
The future is coming on</i>

34:34.480 --> 34:37.313
<i>I ain't happy
I'm feeling glad</i>

34:37.480 --> 34:42.156
<i>I got sunshine in a bag
I'm useless</i>

34:42.320 --> 34:45.915
<i>But not for long
The future is coming on</i>

34:46.080 --> 34:48.993
<i>Is coming on
ls coming on</i>

34:49.159 --> 34:51.514
<i>Coming on
ls coming on</i>

34:51.679 --> 34:53.591
<i>Is coming on
ls coming on</i>

34:54.440 --> 34:57.353
VVow! They're as
miserable <i>as</i> you.

34:58.000 --> 35:01.516
Which means they haven't
eaten a Troll yet.

35:01.680 --> 35:03.637
Now, come on.
Let's go save our friends.

35:03.720 --> 35:04.755
Your friends.

35:04.840 --> 35:07.036
Our friends.
Don't fight it.

35:13.520 --> 35:15.113
(smamwe)

35:15.200 --> 35:16.270
Oh, Barnabus.

35:17.040 --> 35:20.192
You're my only friend
in this whole miserable world.

35:22.040 --> 35:23.314
Dad was right.

35:25.120 --> 35:28.875
Hlnevereven
never ever, never be happy.

35:29.040 --> 35:30.030
(GROANS)

35:30.160 --> 35:31.195
Never

35:31.360 --> 35:35.558
CHEF: Never say never.

35:42.560 --> 35:43.550
(SHRIEKS)

35:45.360 --> 35:46.555
(GROWLING)

35:47.080 --> 35:48.878
Chad.Todd.

35:50.360 --> 35:51.350
(GASPS)

35:51.480 --> 35:53.153
Chef, where did you come from?

35:53.320 --> 35:56.073
My father banished
you 20 years ago.

35:56.240 --> 35:58.356
Have you been standing behind
that plant this whole time?

35:58.520 --> 36:00.318
If only, sire.

36:00.480 --> 36:02.232
No. I've been out
in the wilderness...

36:02.400 --> 36:05.518
thinking of nothing
but how I let you down.

36:07.040 --> 36:09.919
If only there was some way
I could make you feel better.

36:10.080 --> 36:11.070
Well, fat chance!

36:11.240 --> 36:12.514
The only way
I'll ever be happy

36:12.600 --> 36:13.829
is by eating a Troll...

36:14.000 --> 36:15.832
and that ain't gonna
happen, thanks to you.

36:16.000 --> 36:19.277
Ah, but it just might.
Thanks to me.

36:19.440 --> 36:21.078
(TROLL CHOIR SINGING)

36:21.840 --> 36:23.069
(ALL GASPING)

36:29.440 --> 36:31.431
You found the Trolls.

36:31.760 --> 36:32.955
Whoa.
(ALL GASPING)

36:34.440 --> 36:38.559
So this means I might
actually get to be happy!

36:38.720 --> 36:39.676
That's right.

36:39.800 --> 36:41.438
(EXCLAIMING IN DELIGHT)
(TROLLS GASPING)

36:41.560 --> 36:43.437
Of course, everyone
else in Bergen Town

36:43.560 --> 36:45.198
will still be miserable...

36:45.360 --> 36:47.431
but that's not your concern.

36:47.640 --> 36:50.758
I am their king,
so maybe it kinda is.

36:50.920 --> 36:53.116
What exactly
are you proposing?

36:53.280 --> 36:56.398
Bringing back Trollstice?
For everyone?

36:56.720 --> 36:57.710
Hmm...

36:57.800 --> 37:00.110
Yes! That's exactly
what I'm proposing.

37:00.320 --> 37:02.789
Great idea, sire.
Absolutely brilliant.

37:02.880 --> 37:03.950
Aren't you smart?

37:04.120 --> 37:05.110
(CHUCKLES) I guess I am.

37:05.320 --> 37:08.472
And I, your loyal Chef,
will be right behind you.

37:08.640 --> 37:10.472
Holding a knife.
What's that?

37:10.640 --> 37:12.392
Holding a knife,
a spoon, a ladle.

37:12.560 --> 37:14.312
I'm your chef, after all!

37:14.480 --> 37:16.118
Yeah, you sure are!

37:19.160 --> 37:21.231
I'm back!

37:21.560 --> 37:23.278
You, scullery maid,
what's your name?

37:23.440 --> 37:24.430
Uh, Bridget.

37:24.600 --> 37:26.318
Congratulations, ldget.
You work for me now.

37:26.480 --> 37:27.754
So you take
those dishes downstairs

37:27.840 --> 37:29.239
and you start scrubbing.

37:29.400 --> 37:31.391
Yes, Chef.
Thank you, Chef.

37:33.760 --> 37:34.989
(TROLLS SCREAMING)

37:37.240 --> 37:38.594
(ALL WHIMPERING)

37:38.680 --> 37:40.591
Shh. Don't cry,
Mr. Dinkies. Shh!

37:40.680 --> 37:43.354
Guys, Mr. Dinkies
is really freaking out!

37:43.960 --> 37:44.995
(SQUEAKS)

37:45.080 --> 37:49.472
Whoa, whoa! Everyone,
we must all remain calm.

37:49.680 --> 37:51.751
(CHANTING) Comb

37:51.920 --> 37:52.910
That's right.
(GASPS)

37:53.040 --> 37:55.509
A calm Troll
is a tasty Troll.

37:56.680 --> 38:00.275
And you are a key ingredient
in my recipe for success.

38:00.440 --> 38:01.430
(TROLLS GASPING)
You see...

38:01.520 --> 38:04.353
he who controls the Trolls
controls the Kingdom.

38:04.520 --> 38:07.273
And I am that "he!"

38:07.440 --> 38:09.351
You're a dude?
(GRUNTS)

38:11.480 --> 38:12.470
Ahh!

38:13.320 --> 38:14.355
Ooh.

38:14.440 --> 38:17.114
By this time tomorrow,
I'll be queen...

38:17.280 --> 38:18.793
and all of Bergen Town
will get

38:18.880 --> 38:20.473
exactly what they deserve.

38:20.640 --> 38:23.393
True happiness!

38:24.560 --> 38:25.880
(CHEF LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

38:26.160 --> 38:27.195
(CAWING)

38:33.720 --> 38:35.233
Chad.
Todd.

38:41.360 --> 38:42.350
(BOTH GRUNTING)

38:48.040 --> 38:49.758
So where do you think
our friends are?

38:49.920 --> 38:53.311
If I had to guess,
I'd say in a Bergen's stomach.

38:53.760 --> 38:55.319
Could you try to be positive?

38:55.520 --> 38:57.352
Justonce.
You might like it.

38:57.640 --> 38:59.711
Okay. I'm sure
they're not only alive...

38:59.880 --> 39:02.918
but about to be delivered
to us on a silver platter.

39:03.080 --> 39:05.390
(SIGHS) Thank you.
That wasn't so hard, was it?

39:06.560 --> 39:07.550
(CHIMES)

39:07.680 --> 39:08.829
(GASPS) Branch!

39:09.000 --> 39:10.593
Hug time? Seriously?
(SHUSHING)

39:10.760 --> 39:11.909
Listen.

39:12.840 --> 39:14.274
(FLOWERS CHIMING)

39:17.360 --> 39:19.431
This is gonna be
the best Trollstice ever!

39:19.520 --> 39:21.272
Such a great idea I had.

39:22.080 --> 39:24.037
CHEF: Yes. Tomorrow is
Trollstice, everyone.

39:24.120 --> 39:25.190
And it must be perfect!

39:25.280 --> 39:26.315
ALL: Yes, Chef!

39:26.400 --> 39:29.756
Feels great to be ordering
everyone around again.

39:29.960 --> 39:31.030
Branch, look!

39:31.200 --> 39:32.190
They're alive?

39:32.360 --> 39:34.874
And on a silver platter, too.
We were both right.

39:35.040 --> 39:37.111
And to mark the occasion,
Your Highness, look.

39:37.280 --> 39:39.749
I found your old Troll bib.

39:39.920 --> 39:41.479
KING GRISTLE: Oh, wow!
I bet you still fit.

39:42.800 --> 39:44.473
(STRAINING)

39:45.040 --> 39:46.633
(RASPY) Like a glove!

39:46.760 --> 39:48.034
(GROANS)
Ahh...

39:48.320 --> 39:49.754
(LAUGHS)
TROLLS: Shh.

39:50.640 --> 39:51.789
Oh, you think that's funny?

39:51.960 --> 39:53.234
We'll see who's laughing

39:53.320 --> 39:54.640
when I bite
your yummy head off.

39:54.800 --> 39:56.950
When I bite all y'alls
yummy heads off.

39:58.640 --> 39:59.630
Wait a minute.

39:59.720 --> 40:01.711
Chef, this isn't
enough yummy heads

40:01.800 --> 40:03.313
to feed all of Bergen Town.

40:04.160 --> 40:05.719
How are we supposed
to have Trollstice

40:05.840 --> 40:07.433
if there's not enough Trolls?

40:07.600 --> 40:09.637
Oh, there's plenty more
where that came from, sire.

40:09.840 --> 40:11.114
KING GRISTLE: Are you sure?

40:11.280 --> 40:12.395
Because I promised
everyone a Troll.

40:12.480 --> 40:13.595
CHEF: No, no, no, sire!

40:13.800 --> 40:15.154
Everything will be fine.

40:15.320 --> 40:16.833
If I were truly worried...

40:17.000 --> 40:19.116
would I be willing
to do this?

40:19.280 --> 40:20.315
Creek!

40:22.320 --> 40:23.435
(GASPING)

40:23.920 --> 40:25.149
Oh, my first Troll!

40:25.320 --> 40:27.516
Go on, eat, King Gristle.

40:27.680 --> 40:30.638
Enjoy a taste
of true happiness.

40:34.680 --> 40:35.670
(WHIMPERING)

40:35.800 --> 40:36.790
(TROLLS SHUDDERING)

40:37.280 --> 40:38.793
Shouldn't we wait
for Trollstice?

40:38.920 --> 40:39.910
TROLLS: Phew.

40:40.040 --> 40:43.351
Sire, every day is Trollstice
when you have Trolls.

40:47.600 --> 40:49.034
Yeah, I guess.

40:50.800 --> 40:51.790
(SHUDDERING)

40:52.200 --> 40:54.350
But my dad said the first time
should be special.

40:54.520 --> 40:55.715
(TROLLS SIGHING)

40:56.960 --> 40:58.519
Well, you're the king now.
(CREEK GROANING)

40:58.720 --> 41:00.677
Yeah, lam the king.

41:03.560 --> 41:04.709
But I think
I should share this moment

41:04.800 --> 41:06.677
with all the kingdom.

41:06.840 --> 41:08.558
(GRUNTS) Eat it!
(TROLLS GASPING)

41:08.640 --> 41:09.630
Mmm.

41:09.720 --> 41:10.835
Oh' my God!
No!

41:11.000 --> 41:11.990
Yes!

41:12.840 --> 41:14.513
(PLAYING MARIACHI MUSIC)

41:15.320 --> 41:16.549
(CHOKING)

41:17.040 --> 41:18.030
Mmm.

41:18.200 --> 41:20.714
Idget, lock these Trolls
in your room

41:20.800 --> 41:22.711
and guard them with your life.

41:24.240 --> 41:25.230
Yes, Chef.

41:25.400 --> 41:26.390
(KING GRISTLE MOANING)

41:26.520 --> 41:27.510
Yes. Yes, I know.

41:27.680 --> 41:28.829
Branch, we have to save him!

41:29.000 --> 41:30.673
Save him from what?
His stomach?

41:30.880 --> 41:32.234
We didn't see him chew.
We didn't see him swallow!

41:32.400 --> 41:33.470
Face it, Poppy.

41:33.560 --> 41:34.914
Sometimes people go
into other people's mouths...

41:35.080 --> 41:36.070
and they don't come out.

41:36.200 --> 41:38.999
If we go after Creek now,
we're going to get eaten.

41:39.400 --> 41:40.595
I'm sorry...

41:40.760 --> 41:42.159
but it's too late for him.

41:42.320 --> 41:43.310
KING GRISTLE: Mmm-mmm-mmm.

41:50.040 --> 41:50.996
Huh. Poppy!

41:51.080 --> 41:52.150
(GRUNTING)

42:00.920 --> 42:01.910
(GRUNTING)

42:19.120 --> 42:21.111
CHEF: Scullery maid!
(GASPS)

42:22.240 --> 42:23.435
(GROANING)

42:23.920 --> 42:26.594
CHEF: Wash these pots
and pans for Trollstice.

42:26.760 --> 42:28.592
The king's inviting everyone.

42:28.760 --> 42:30.114
<i>Except you.</i>

42:31.720 --> 42:33.040
(SOBBING)

42:51.760 --> 42:56.994
<i>(SINGING) I've been alone
with you inside my mind</i>

42:59.560 --> 43:03.155
<i>And in my dreams
I've kissed your lips</i>

43:03.960 --> 43:06.679
<i>A thousand times</i>

43:07.520 --> 43:12.959
<i>I sometimes see you
pass outside my door</i>

43:15.160 --> 43:16.275
<i>Hello</i>

43:18.600 --> 43:22.514
<i>Is it me you're looking for?</i>

43:23.200 --> 43:26.591
<i>I can see it in your eyes</i>

43:26.760 --> 43:29.957
<i>I can see it in your smile</i>

43:31.280 --> 43:33.954
<i>You're all I've ever wanted</i>

43:34.880 --> 43:38.510
<i>And my arms are open wide</i>

43:38.680 --> 43:40.512
<i>'Cause you know
just what to say</i>

43:40.720 --> 43:42.711
You're all the idiots! I have
to do everything myself.

43:42.960 --> 43:44.792
<i>And you know
just what to do</i>

43:44.880 --> 43:45.915
I have to get out of bed,

43:46.000 --> 43:47.877
I'm supposed to put my own
clothes on, tie my own shoes.

43:48.040 --> 43:49.633
<i>And I want to
tell you so much</i>

43:52.280 --> 43:53.998
<i>I love you</i>

43:56.400 --> 43:58.357
(SOBBING)

44:02.520 --> 44:03.715
(SNORING)

44:07.000 --> 44:08.638
Oh, she's in love
with the king.

44:08.800 --> 44:11.633
What are you talking about?
Bergens don't have feelings.

44:11.800 --> 44:13.791
Well, maybe you don't know
everything about the Bergens.

44:14.000 --> 44:15.354
Now let's go.

44:21.920 --> 44:23.672
Guys! ALL; poppy!

44:23.840 --> 44:27.037
<i>(ALL SINGING) Celebrate
good times, come on</i>

44:27.200 --> 44:29.316
<i>It's a celebration</i>

44:29.520 --> 44:30.840
(SHUSHING)

44:31.200 --> 44:33.714
<i>(SINGING) There's</i> a <i>party
going on right here</i>

44:33.880 --> 44:36.759
No! There is not a party
going on right here.

44:39.280 --> 44:40.918
The sooner we get you
guys out of here...

44:41.080 --> 44:42.593
The sooner
we can save Creek!

44:42.760 --> 44:44.273
What?
(GASPS)

44:44.360 --> 44:45.430
Hello?

44:45.600 --> 44:46.590
(ALL GASPING)

44:47.120 --> 44:49.191
Is it me you're looking for?

44:49.520 --> 44:51.033
(SNORING)
ALL: Phew...

44:51.360 --> 44:53.431
I know you're looking for the
cupcakes and rainbows here...

44:53.600 --> 44:55.193
but let's face it,
Creek's been eaten.

44:55.360 --> 44:56.680
They put him in a taco!

44:56.880 --> 44:58.109
It was horrible.

44:58.280 --> 45:00.112
Sorry, Poppy.
Creek's gone.

45:01.920 --> 45:05.390
Poppy, how could you possibly
think Creek's still alive?

45:05.560 --> 45:07.039
I don't think he's alive.

45:07.120 --> 45:09.634
I hope he's alive,
and that's enough.

45:09.800 --> 45:12.110
How do you always look
on the bright side?

45:12.280 --> 45:13.953
There is no bright side here.
None!

45:14.120 --> 45:15.554
There's always a bright side.

45:15.720 --> 45:17.791
Hey! Where do you think
you're going?

45:18.240 --> 45:19.310
(TROLLS SCREAMING)

45:21.920 --> 45:23.957
Glitter!
No! Get back in your cage!

45:24.320 --> 45:25.355
(BRIDGET GRUNTING)

45:25.480 --> 45:26.470
(TROLLS CLAMORING)

45:26.600 --> 45:27.829
Chef's gonna be so mad!

45:27.960 --> 45:29.234
(SCREAMING)

45:29.320 --> 45:30.310
No!

45:31.160 --> 45:32.878
(GRUNTING)
